OL,3,CProtest over electricity price hike
OL,4,Cthat 'will ruin lives'
OL,6,FAnother protestor, Debbie Le Page,
OL,7,Fsays more expensive electricity bills
OL,8,Fare putting vulnerable islanders at
OL,9,Frisk, including her own mother.
OL,11,FShe explains: "I have my elderly mum
OL,12,Fliving with me. She's got a telly from
OL,13,Fseven in the morning to 11 at night.
OL,14,FThat's her company, apart from us.
OL,16,F"Her heating is on just as long and we
OL,17,Fwent to electric central heating after
OL,18,Fbeing persuaded that it was going to
OL,19,Fbe the cheapest and the most
OL,20,Feconomical.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/10
