OL,3,CProtest over electricity price hike
OL,4,Cthat 'will ruin lives'
OL,6,F"Of course it's not. Well, I can't not
OL,7,Fput it on because she's poorly."
OL,9,FAhead of the proposed rise, Guernsey
OL,10,Fcustomers currently pay 23.89p per
OL,11,Funit, compared to 21.66p in Jersey and
OL,12,F25.73p in the UK.
OL,14,FThe quarterly standing charge is also
OL,15,Fgoing up from #68.25 to #86.75,
OL,16,Fmeaning all customers will pay around
OL,17,Fan extra 20p per day on their bill.
