OL,3,CProtest over electricity price hike
OL,4,Cthat 'will ruin lives'
OL,6,FIn a statement, Guernsey Electricity's
OL,7,FChief Executive Officer, Alan Bates,
OL,8,Fsays the rises are needed to help the
OL,9,Fcompany improve its infrastructure and
OL,10,Frepay debt.
OL,12,FHe explains: "Guernsey Electricity
OL,13,FLimited absolutely understands the
OL,14,Fstrength of feeling amongst some
OL,15,Fislanders following the recent
OL,16,Fannouncement of an increase in
OL,17,Felectricity tariffs and we appreciate
OL,18,Fthat this will have an impact on
OL,19,Fcustomers who are already struggling
OL,20,Fwith the cost of living.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/10
